Non vegetarian eating & Scriptures... (Excerpt from message of Shri Datta Swami)  Once, a devotee asked Mohammad for the way to please the God. The first thing mentioned by Mohammad (Sallam) to please God was not to kill any innocent living being like bird and animal. He told that if you kill one living being it is equal to killing the entire humanity.  You cannot justify killing the animals for the purpose of eating protein-flesh because God, the capable administrator who created this humanity, already served the purpose by creating protein rich oils. Hence, your killing of animals is without cause and is not acceptable to the concept of Mohammed.  Jesus is seen with love on a lamb in His hands and this indicates the love on animals.  Veda says to kill the animal nature present in yourself but not the actual animal in yajna (Manyuhpashuh…).  Even the modern medical education recommends the natural proteins in vegetables to be better for health than the synthesized proteins in the animal flesh. Science is the principle of nature, which indicates the will of God because nature is creation of God only.  Hindu Manusmruti says that the greatest justice is not to kill any living being (Ahimsaaparamodharmah…).  Buddha started the revolution by opposing the killing of animals and He is the embodiment of love and kindness to animals and birds. He left the home on seeing a bird wounded by arrow.  The tsunami in the sea and the quakes in the earth are only the anger of God in killing the life in water and the life on the land respectively. The sea with its wave-hands is always warning the people not to kill the poor harmless aquatic creatures like fish etc., for the sake of food. Great combination. I like that you use cups for measurement so that people who are just starting cooking can follow without problems. One suggestion andi,  kothimeera should never be cooked especially in pressure cooker . It loses all its fragrance. You should add kothimeera to wet curries after everything is done and steam is all gone . In  roti pachadi you can add when you are grinding . In vepudu you can add towards the end before you switch off. Since there is no water in vepudu curries it will not destroy kothimeera qualities. Basically kothimeera should stay green. When it turns grayish it basically does nothing.
